Space Mission Control :
-------------------------
Swift Web CRUD Application | iOS Course 2026
----------------------------------------------

A full-stack web application built with Swift 6.2, Hummingbird 2, and SQLite to manage a global registry of interstellar space missions.

📖 Project Overview
The purpose of this application is to demonstrate a complete Model-View-Controller (MVC) architecture using the Swift programming language. The app allows users to catalog and track space exploration data, including mission names, aerospace agencies, planetary destinations, and launch years.


🛠 Features & Requirements :
----------------------------

Data Model: A custom SpaceMission struct with 5 fields (ID, Name, Agency, Destination, Year) conforming to Codable and Sendable.

Full CRUD Operations:

Create: Add missions via a validated web form.

Read: View all registered missions in a dynamic, responsive table.

Update: Modify mission parameters through a dedicated edit interface.

Delete: Remove missions from the registry with a single click.

Search & Filter : A functional search bar that filters the mission list by Name or Destination using URL query parameters.

Server-Side Validation : Implementation of guard statements to prevent empty entries and ensure launch years are logically valid (post-1950).

Enhanced UI/UX : Styled with Pico CSS, featuring a navigation bar, organized grid layouts, and intuitive action buttons.

Routes:
-------
- `GET /`: View all missions (supports `?search=` query).
- `POST /add`: Create a new mission.
- `GET /edit/:id`: View the edit form for a mission.
- `POST /update/:id`: Update mission details.
- `POST /delete/:id`: Delete a mission.

⚙️ How to Run :
----------------
1- Open the terminal in your GitHub Codespace.

2- Build the project: ./build.sh

3- Start the server: ./run.sh

4- Access the app via the port 8080 popup.